trans-unit.source: Provides a collection of <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.EventMappingSettings"></xref> objects.
This class cannot be inherited.
The <xref:System.Web.Configuration.EventMappingSettings> class corresponds to the `eventMappings` configuration file element.
The `eventMappings` element allows you to assign friendly names to event sources.
These names are then used to associate event sources with the related event consumers, called providers, in the `rules` subsection of the `healthMonitoring` section of the configuration file.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.EventMappingSettingsCollection"></xref> class.

The <xref:System.Web.Configuration.HealthMonitoringSection.EventMappings%2A> property of the <xref:System.Web.Configuration.HealthMonitoringSection> class always contains an instance of the <xref:System.Web.Configuration.EventMappingSettingsCollection>.
Use this instance, rather than creating your own instance of the class.
Adds an <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.EventMappingSettings"></xref> object to the collection.
The collection must not already contain a <xref:System.Web.Configuration.EventMappingSettings> object with the same name.
An <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.EventMappingSettings"></xref> object to add to the collection.
The <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.EventMappingSettings"></xref> object to add already exists in the collection, or the collection is read-only.
Removes all <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.EventMappingSettings"></xref> objects from the collection.
This method inserts a `clear` directive into the appropriate section of the configuration file to clear all references to elements defined in a higher-level configuration file.
All elements defined in the appropriate section of the current configuration file are removed.
Indicates whether the collection contains an <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.EventMappingSettings"></xref> object with the specified name.
This method returns `false` if the specified name does not exist.
The name of an <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.EventMappingSettings"></xref> object in the collection.
`true` if the collection contains an <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.EventMappingSettings"></xref> object with the specified name; otherwise, `false`.
Returns the index of the specified <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.EventMappingSettings"></xref> object.
The name of an <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.EventMappingSettings"></xref> object in the collection.
The index of the specified <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.EventMappingSettings"></xref> object, or -1 if the object is not found in the collection.
Adds the specified <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.EventMappingSettings"></xref> object to the specified index point in the collection.
If the index parameter equals the number of items in the collection, then the entry is appended to the end of the collection.
A valid index of an <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.EventMappingSettings"></xref> object in the collection.
The <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.EventMappingSettings"></xref> object to insert into the collection.
The <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.EventMappingSettings"></xref> object to add already exists in the collection, the index is invalid, or the collection is read-only.
Gets or sets the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.EventMappingSettings"></xref> object at the specified index location.
A valid index of an <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.EventMappingSettings"></xref> object in the collection.
The <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.EventMappingSettings"></xref> object at the specified index, or `null` if there is no object at that index.
Gets the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.EventMappingSettings"></xref> object based on the specified key in the collection.
The name of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.EventMappingSettings"></xref> object contained in the collection.
An <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.EventMappingSettings"></xref> object.
Removes an <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.EventMappingSettings"></xref> object from the collection.
This method inserts a `remove` element into the appropriate section of the configuration file for any element defined in a higher-level configuration file.
If the element is defined in the appropriate section of the current configuration file, its entry is removed from the configuration file.
The object to remove must exist in the collection.
The name of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.EventMappingSettings"></xref> to remove from the collection.
There is no <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.EventMappingSettings"></xref> object with the specified key in the collection, the element has already been removed, or the collection is read-only.
Removes an <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.EventMappingSettings"></xref> object from the collection.
This method inserts a `remove` element into the appropriate section of the configuration file for any element defined in a higher-level configuration file.
If the element is defined in the appropriate section of the current configuration file, its entry is removed from the configuration file.
The object to remove must exist in the collection.
The index of an <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.EventMappingSettings"></xref> object in the collection.
There is no <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.EventMappingSettings"></xref> object with the specified index in the collection, the element has already been removed, or the collection is read-only.
